    "src": "https://res.cloudinary.com/loresec/image/upload/v1493770855/pyramidpeakmap_prclna.jpg",
    "width": 910
  }), mdx("p", null, "This is where the fun begins. I wouldn\u2019t receive the watch until the afternoon that I planned to leave for Death Valley, and I intended to start the hike when I arrived about 7:30 PM. I was going to haul my overnight gear, food, and water at least a mile from the road, keeping with back country camping regulations, set up camp, get a good night\u2019s sleep, and head for the summit in the early morning."), mdx("p", null, "I needed to get the map shown above converted into a GPX file I could upload to my watch, and I had to get it all ready to before I even had the watch with me. So what did I do?"), mdx("p", null, "This is where HikingGuy.com enters the picture. In his post titled ", mdx("a", {
    parentName: "p",
    "href": "https://hikingguy.com/how-to-hike/creating-a-hike-garmin-gps/"
